.TH logmsg "" "" "System Administration"
.PC "Hold \*(CO Login Message"
.B /etc/logmsg
.PP
.II "login message"
The file
.B /etc/logmsg
holds the message that \*(CO displays to prompt the user to log in.
The superuser
.B bin
can edit this message to whatever she prefers.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "Administering COHERENT" administe
.SH Notes
.II "beep^remove from login message"
.II "bell^remove from login message"
The default message consists of the bell character
.B <ctrl-G>
followed by the text
.BR "Coherent login:" .
If the bell annoys you, simply delete the
.B <ctrl-G>
from
.BR /etc/logmsg .
